My name's Lana. \|I'm a mercenary. \|Until about six
months ago, \.I was part of the Blacktooth Bandits.
I was only thirteen when Blacktooth Bill recruited me
into his gang. \|He said I had a lot of potential. \|He
said that I saw things that others didn't.
He was right. \|I was the best scout that the Blacktooth
Bandits ever had.
Bill's second in command was a man named Taggart. \|
However much faith Bill had in my abilities, \.Taggart
thought I could do so much more.
Taggart was a founding member of the gang. \|A lot of
us figured that he could have taken the top spot
whenever he wanted.
But, \.for whatever reason, \.Taggart was content to
always be second best to Bill. \|I think Taggart knew
how dangerous it was to be the face of the gang. \|He
didn't want his face on the wanted posters.
Things were good for a while. \|The gang was respected
and feared, \.wherever we went. \|Our bellies and our
coinpurses were always full.
It didn't last. \|We somehow managed to become notorious
enough to attract the attention of Inquisitor Illara.
\|She started quartering soldiers in all of our usual
villages.
Bill somehow got it in his head that we'd be able to
fight an Inquisitor's army head on. \|We militarized
rapidly.
It turns out that a ragtag group of warriors in
mismatched armor is no match for a well funded,
\.organized military force backed by one of the most
powerful witches in the country.
